<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma kittanae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Onosma kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially described as endemic to Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Stevanovic, V." journalOrPublisher="Plant Syst. Evol." pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="149 - 170" refId="B7670950" refString="Stevanovic, V., Tan, K., Iatrou, G., 2003. Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. -obligate serpentine endemics. Plant Syst. Evol. 242: 149 - 170" title="Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. - obligate serpentine endemics" volume="242" year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stevanović">Stevanovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), until 
<bibRefCitation author="Teppner, H." journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="77 - 97" refId="B7670067" refString="Teppner, H., Karl, R., 2017. Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae). Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark 147: 77 - 97" title="Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae)" volume="147" year="2017">Teppner and Karl (2017)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out its similarities to 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. pavlovae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="pavlovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. pavlovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Petrova &amp; Kit Tan (
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="bulgarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. bulgarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D. Pavlova non 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Velenovský">Velenovsky</normalizedToken>
) from Bulgaria and treated the latter as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. kittanae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species remains a rare, range-restricted Balkan endemic confined to the serpentine substrates of south Bulgaria and NE Greece. In Greece, only two localities were known so far: around the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">locus classicus</emphasis>
in Nomos Evrou (
<bibRefCitation author="Stevanovic, V." journalOrPublisher="Plant Syst. Evol." pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="149 - 170" refId="B7670950" refString="Stevanovic, V., Tan, K., Iatrou, G., 2003. Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. -obligate serpentine endemics. Plant Syst. Evol. 242: 149 - 170" title="Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. - obligate serpentine endemics" volume="242" year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stevanović">Stevanovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Teppner, H." journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="77 - 97" refId="B7670067" refString="Teppner, H., Karl, R., 2017. Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae). Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark 147: 77 - 97" title="Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae)" volume="147" year="2017">Teppner and Karl 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and between Organi and Chloi Villages of Nomos Rodopis (
<bibRefCitation author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 24 (2): 263 - 292" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669441" refString="Strid, A., 2018. New floristic records in the Balkans: 36. Phytologia Balcanica, 24 (2): 263-292" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 36" year="2018">Strid 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Our third, new locality (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F7677582" captionText="Figure 10. Onosma kittanae from Nomos Xanthis (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640536" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">10</figureCitation>
) forms the westernmost distribution border for the species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F7677586" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution map of Onosma kittanae, Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum and Silene fetlerii in Greece and Bulgaria." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656688" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">11</figureCitation>
). According to the [B1ab(ii iii iv) + 2ab(ii iii iv)] criteria, 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. kittanae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits the Endangered Category at national level (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32 pp" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668800" refString="IUCN, , 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32pp" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
